Subject: Internet speed decreased on MacOS 15.0 Darwin
Description:
Hello,

Customer name is PrivatBank.
They reported that on one MacOS 15 Darwin user is complaining about low internet speed.
Enable/Disable Intercept VPN traffic did not help with this issue.
I will attach logs and screenshots under this post, please look into it.
After EPP client was deleted, internet speed started to be fast.
What_We_Know__c:
Reported that on one MacOS 15 Darwin user is complaining about low internet speed. Enable/Disable Intercept VPN traffic did not help with this issue.

2025.03.05 Update:
Customer reproduced this issue with the latest macOS EPP client. Attached are logs and screenshots.
Next_Steps__c:
New epp client logs captured from macOS epp client version 3.0.4.1006 were submitted to R&D team to analyze and provide new feedback.

2025.03.05 Update:
Customer feedback with logs and screenshots submitted to R&D for analysis.

The update from our partner on this case is as follows:

2025.03.17 Update:
"The status of this case is follow:
If the Intercept VPN traffic is ON - customer have issues with Google Meet, that is why they disabled this option.
But, without the Intercept VPN traffic option, there is internet speed issue occurs on several computers.
And unfortunately, customer cannot enable Intercept VPN traffic there because of Google meet issue.
So, if we will fix the issue with Google meet (#429094) this issue should be fixed as well."

The above is referring to ADO: https://dev.azure.com/NetwrixCorporation/CoSoSys-EPP/_workitems/edit/367786
Solution_Comment__c:
The partner agreed that the ticket can be closed at this moment.
"If turning on the Intercept VPN will not help in the future - I will make a follow-up."
